\end{equation}
\lean{chebyshev_T_leadingCoeff}
\leanok

By Vieta's formulas, the coefficient of $x^{N-k}$ in $P_N(x; \varphi)$ is $(-1)^k e_k(r_0, \ldots, r_{N-1})$, and the coefficient of $x^{N-k}$ in $T_N(x)/2^{N-1}$ is $(-1)^k e_k(\xi_0, \ldots, \xi_{N-1})$.
